Go port copyright (c) 2026 the jargo authors.


Third-party dependencies
------------------------

The WebRTC transport is built on the Pion stack (https://github.com/pion),
copyright (c) The Pion community, licensed under the MIT License. This includes
github.com/pion/webrtc and github.com/pion/opus (a pure-Go Opus codec).

Voice activity and end-of-turn detection use the ONNX Runtime via
github.com/yalue/onnxruntime_go (MIT License). The ONNX Runtime itself
(https://onnxruntime.ai, MIT License) is supplied by the operator and is not
distributed with jargo.


Embedded models
---------------

jargo embeds two ONNX models, used unmodified:

  - Silero VAD (audio/vad/silero_vad.onnx), from
    https://github.com/snakers4/silero-vad, copyright (c) Silero Team,
    licensed under the MIT License.

  - Smart Turn v3 (audio/turn/smart-turn-v3.2-cpu.onnx), from
    https://github.com/pipecat-ai/smart-turn, copyright (c) Daily, licensed
    under the BSD 2-Clause License.

The Whisper-style log-mel feature extraction in audio/turn/whisper.go is a
numpy-free Go reimplementation of the math in Hugging Face Transformers'
WhisperFeatureExtractor (https://github.com/huggingface/transformers,
copyright (c) The HuggingFace Team, Apache License 2.0).
